Module hu.unipannon.virt.plot
Package hu.unipannon.virt.plot.frame.vertical

Class VTickLabels

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.Parent
        • javafx.scene.Group
          • hu.unipannon.virt.plot.frame.Container
            • hu.unipannon.virt.plot.frame.vertical.VTickLabels
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
    public class VTickLabels
extends Container
    The VTickLabels class implements the generation of the tick label objects based on the divisor points, as well as contains functions to set the graphical properties of the labels. The class is a container and is usually bound to the VerticalAxis.
    Author:
    Tóth Bálint
    See Also:
    VerticalAxis

      • setDivisors

        public void setDivisors​(double[] divisors,
                        java.lang.String[] labels)
        Setter for the divisor points and the labels displayed at those points. Divisors must be normalized to the [0;1] interval. The two arrays must be of same size.
        Parameters:
        divisors - normalized divisor points.
        labels - labels for the division points.
